{"id": "feb24502-fbc2-4a79-ba5c-300ad3aeae1a", "url": "http://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/resource?r=smb_cladocera_tr698", "archive": "https://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/archive.do?r=smb_cladocera_tr698", "published": "2021-04-16T11:33:28.000Z", "created": null, "updated": "2025-11-09T01:12:23.179Z", "core": "occurrence", "extensions": [], "statistics": {"Event": 0, "absence": 0, "dropped": 0, "Occurrence": 857, "DNADerivedData": 0, "MeasurementOrFact": 0}, "extent": "POLYGON((-64.05 44.58333,-64.03333 44.58333,-64.03333 44.61666,-64.05 44.61666,-64.05 44.58333))", "title": "MEL: Marine cladocera collected from St. Margarets Bay between May to November, 1967-1969", "citation": "Platt T (2013): MEL: Marine cladocera collected from St. Margarets Bay between May to November, 1967-1969. v1.5. Canadian node of the Ocean Biogeographic Information System (OBIS Canada). Dataset/Occurrence. http://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/resource?r=smb_cladocera_tr698&amp;v=1.5", "citation_id": null, "abstract": "Population dynamics of Cladocera were studied from 1967 to 1969, as a part of a multidisciplinary program designed to study biological and physical processes pertinent to the marine food web in St. Margaret\u2019s Bay, Nova Scotia. Samples were collected using plankton ring nets with the objective to examine seasonal variation in abundance of important species/taxa of zooplankton. This resource focuses on cladocera collected during preliminary sampling in 1967 and during the multidisciplinary program in 1968 and 1969.", "intellectualrights": "This work is licensed under a  Creative Commons Attribution (CC-BY) 4.0 License", "feed": {"id": "6ae5ad4f-2a01-43bd-9fb4-cc9c7f38f105", "url": "http://ipt.vliz.be/obiscanada/rss.do"}, "institutes": [{"name": "Fisheries and Oceans Canada \u2013 Bedford Institute of Oceanography", "oceanexpert_id": 5070, "oceanexpert_parent_id": 19196}, {"name": "Bedford Institute of Oceanography  \u2014 Marine Ecology Laboratory", "oceanexpert_id": 19619, "oceanexp